ParameterizedPrimitive.Branch, ParameterizedPrimitive.Do, ParameterizedPrimitive.Literal, ParameterizedPrimitive.Loop, ParameterizedPrimitive.PlusLoop
public class ParameterizedPrimitive
extends com.SoftWoehr.FIJI.base.desktop.shell.Primitive
implements SoftWoehr, verbose

ParameterizedPrimitive is an on-the-fly Primitive which we declare to provide special runtimes to be compiled by special compilation semantics, e.g., the runtime of compiled 'to'.

Version:
$Revision: 1.1.1.1 $
Author:
$Author: jwoehr $

validate

public boolean validate()
Validate that object and object class are instanced and that object class equals declared object class. The validation check presumes the programmer was right, i.e., that the declared object class is what is intended. This method validate() thus only guards against runtime non-instantiation or instantiation with the wrong type of object. Cf. engine.runtimeTo() which calls validate() but doesn't compare to class Value because it's assumed that the code creating the primitive knew what class was meant.
Returns:
